'''Teškoto''' or '''Teshkoto''' ({{lang-mk|Тешкото}}, "the hard one"), is a folk dance from western [[Macedonia (region)|Macedonia]], specifically from the [[Mijaks|Mijak ethnographic region]]. It is a war dance, with origins in antique history.<ref name="Damianopoulos2012">{{cite book|author=Ernest N. Damianopoulos|title=The Macedonians: Their Past and Present|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5RjGAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA189|date=15 February 2012|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|isbn=978-1-137-01190-9|pages=189–}}</ref> This folk dance has inspired many artists and poets (for example [[Blaze Koneski]]'s poem ''Teškoto'').<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soros.org.mk/konkurs/076/angver/Teskoto.html |title=Teškoto (The Hard One) |accessdate=2008-10-14}}</ref> The famous Bulgarian singer [[Veselin Marinov]] has a song with the same name.

